public abstract static class AbstractAssignmentChecker.ClassBodyInfo<This extends AbstractAssignmentChecker.ClassBodyInfo<This>>
extends java.lang.Object
A data structure containing relevant information needed for performing initialization checking of a class declaration. These objects form a stack, since class declarations can be nested.

    • outerLocalsUsed

      public final java.util.Set<LocalInstance> outerLocalsUsed
      The LocalInstances from the outer class body that are used during the declaration of the current class. This is used to populate localsUsedInClassBodies.

    • localsUsedInClassBodies

      public final java.util.Map<ClassBody,​java.util.Set<LocalInstance>> localsUsedInClassBodies
      Maps ClassBodys to the LocalInstances of those local variables declared in the current CodeNode that are used by inner classes.

      If outerLocalsUsed maps C to S, then the class body C is an inner class declared in the current code declaration, and S is the set of LocalInstances that are defined in the current code declaration and used in the declaration of the class C.

      This information is used to ensure that local variables are definitely assigned before the class declaration of C.

    • localDeclarations

      public final java.util.Set<LocalInstance> localDeclarations
      The LocalInstances that we have seen declarations for in the current class. This set allows us to determine which local instances are being used before they are declared (e.g., if they are used in their own initialization) or are locals declared in an enclosing class.
